getDAOUpdated

public long getDAOUpdated()
Get the timestamp that was last set with setDAOUpdated(). This timestamp is never set by the library. This is included purely as a way for developers to set a modification timestamp on the DAO for their own purposes. This will return null unless you set it with setDAOUpdated(). This does NOT return the updated timestamp of the actualy element in Box.

Returns:
The last DAOUpdated timestamp set.

setDAOUpdated

public void setDAOUpdated(long daoUpdated)
Set a timestamp to indicate that the DAO has been updated. This is never used by the library itself. It is simply included as a convenience for developers to set an object-update timestamp if needed. You can retrieve the value set here through getDAOUpdated().

Parameters:
daoUpdated - DAO object updated timestamp.
